title: 40 kids under age of 1 die every day in Maharashtra
description: Approximately 40 infants under the age of one die every day in Maharashtra, with two-thirds of these deaths occurring in newborns less than a month old. Prematurity, low birth weight, and respiratory distress are the leading causes of neonatal death. The rise in hospital deliveries, without a proportional increase in healthcare workforce and infrastructure, has contributed to the increase in infant mortality rates.

title: Ajit Pawar replaces BJP's Chandrakant Patil as Pune guardian minister
description: Deputy CM Ajit Pawar has been appointed as the guardian minister for Pune, replacing BJP leader Chandrakant Patil. This follows Pawar's absence from a state Cabinet meeting and his meeting with NCP ministers at his residence, indicating his dissatisfaction with the delay in appointing guardian ministers for various districts. The CM announced a new list of guardian ministers for 12 districts, with Patil becoming the guardian minister for Solapur and Amravati.

title: ED raids Sanjay Singh in liquor case, arrests him
description: AAP's Rajya Sabha MP, Sanjay Singh, has been arrested by the Enforcement Directorate as part of its investigation into the Delhi excise policy. Singh is accused of being involved in the alleged corruption in the distribution of liquor vends by the Arvind Kejriwal government. The arrest comes after searches were conducted at Singh's residence and other premises. Singh has denied the charges, calling his arrest "political vendetta."

title: 10 dead, 22 armymen among 82 missing in Sikkim flash floods
description: A flash flood in North Sikkim caused by a glacial lake outburst flood has resulted in at least 10 deaths and 82 people missing. The flood has caused extensive damage, washing away bridges and roads and cutting off communication lines. Army personnel and vehicles have also been affected, and search operations are currently underway. The Sikkim government has declared a disaster, and emergency services have been mobilized in the affected areas.

title: NewsClick chief in 7-day police custody; 16 media bodies write to CJI
description: NewsClick founder Prabir Purkayastha and HR head Amit Chakravarty have been sent to police custody for seven days. They were arrested in a case filed under UAPA after allegations that the portal was paid to support Chinese propaganda. Sixteen journalist bodies have appealed to the Chief Justice of India, seeking intervention regarding the police raids on journalists' houses.

title: Neeraj Chopra overcomes Chinese ‘goof-up’ to defend title
description: The javelin final proved to be a less-than-pleasant experience for Neeraj Chopra. Despite an impressive initial throw surpassing the 85m mark, it went unrecorded due to an electronic distance measurement glitch reported by officials. Neeraj had to make another throw, and he did so, regaining the lead with a distance of 84.49m on his second attempt.

title: MP, MLA immunity important, but graft is another matter: SC
description: The Supreme Court of India has stated that it will not limit the immunity and privileges enjoyed by MPs and MLAs for their actions within Parliament or assembly. However, the court will review a 25-year-old ruling to determine if lawmakers involved in "cash-for-vote" corruption should be protected by these privileges. The outcome of this review appears to be leaning towards treating bribery as a separate offense unrelated to legislative immunity.

title: Now, teachers join row over IIT-Bombay's 'veg tables' policy
description: The decision to segregate vegetarian students in an IIT-Bombay mess and impose a fine on a student protesting against it has received backlash from teachers. They believe that the fine is disgraceful and that the idea of purity and segregation based on food is a social illness. One professor also argued that government spaces cannot institutionalize segregation, as eating non-vegetarian food is not illegal.

title: 'Goonda tax' not paid, MLA's aides dig up 7-km road stretch in UP
description: A group claiming to be associates of a local MLA in Shahjahanpur, India, dug up and destroyed a 7km road after the contractor refused to pay a "goonda tax." The contractor said that the MLA's representative obstructed the construction and damaged public property. An inquiry has been initiated by the district magistrate. The local MLA denied the allegations, stating that the contractor used low-quality material and may have damaged the road themselves.

title: Hindu marriage not valid without ‘saat pheras’, says HC
description: The Allahabad High Court has ruled that a Hindu marriage is not valid without the 'saptapadi' ceremony, which involves taking seven rounds around the sacred fire. The court quashed the proceedings of a complaint case where a husband accused his estranged wife of solemnizing her second marriage without obtaining a divorce. The court stated that the 'saptapadi' ceremony is an essential ingredient for a valid marriage under Hindu law.

title: New bus shelter stolen in a week from busy Bengaluru road
description: Within a week of its installation, a Rs 10 lakh stainless-steel bus shelter on Cunnigham Road in Bengaluru has been stolen by miscreants. A complaint was filed a month after the theft, and the police have registered a case. The missing bus shelter was used by hundreds of commuters, and now only a small shelter remains in its place.

title: 41% of amphibian species worldwide threatened with extinction: Study
description: A study by global experts has found that 41% of amphibian species worldwide are at risk of extinction. The study, published in Nature, attributes habitat loss and climate change as major drivers of the decline. Between 2004 and 2022, over 300 amphibians have become closer to extinction, with climate change being the primary threat for 39% of these species. The study also reveals that 93% of all threatened species are affected by habitat destruction and degradation.

title: Army set for massive drill to test new-generation weapons, tech
description: The Indian Army is preparing for a large-scale combat exercise called "Trishakti Prahar" in Rajasthan. The exercise aims to test new-generation weapons and technologies, validate new concepts in long-range firepower, and incorporate lessons from the Russia-Ukraine war. Over 30,000 troops, tanks, howitzers, helicopters, fighter jets, and other aircraft from the Indian Air Force and Navy will participate.

title: ‘Creamy layer’ income cap unlikely to be upped soon
description: The Indian government is hesitant to increase the income ceiling for the Other Backward Classes (OBC) creamy layer due to concerns of resentment. Currently, an OBC family earning over Rs 8 lakh is considered "creamy layer" and ineligible for job and education quotas. The government believes that Rs 8 lakh is already a high enough bar and fears that raising it further may lead to copycat demands from other sections.

title: Did Nepal earthquake trigger Sikkim flash flood? Scientists to investigate
No 2nd innings, ‘super over’ for Chandrayaan-3 mission
description: India's Chandrayaan-3 mission, which involved the Vikram lander and Pragyan rover, has not woken up after experiencing a second lunar night. While the chances of them waking up again are slim, the option is not being closed. The mission has already collected sufficient data from the propulsion module payload, SHAPE, which studies habitable planet-like features of Earth. Despite the setback, the mission has been successful in providing new insights into lunar soil properties.

title: Happy World Teachers' Day 2023: Wishes, messages, quotes, images
description: World Teachers' Day, celebrated on October 5th every year, is a global event that recognizes and honors the contributions of teachers to society. The theme for World Teachers' Day 2023 is "The teachers we need for the education we want: The global imperative to reverse the teacher shortage." It highlights the critical challenge of a shortage of qualified teachers around the world. On this day, people express gratitude and appreciation for their teachers through wishes, messages, and quotes. Various activities are organized to celebrate and honor teachers, including teacher appreciation awards, workshops, student performances, and community outreach projects.

title: 'A man is a man ...' : Sunak's take on gender debate sparks row
description: UK Prime Minister Rishi Sunak and Indian-American politician Vivek Ramaswamy have both expressed controversial views on transgender rights. Sunak stated that individuals cannot be any sex they want to be, emphasizing that "a man is a man, and a woman is a woman." Ramaswamy believes that gender dysphoria should be considered a mental health disorder and supports informing parents if their children change their gender identity at school.

title: Rahul Gandhi's surprise gift 'Noorie' for mother Sonia Gandhi
description: Rahul Gandhi, a Congress leader in India, surprised his mother Sonia Gandhi by gifting a Jack Russell Terrier puppy named 'Noorie'. In a video shared on his YouTube channel, Rahul is seen meeting the puppy during a visit to Goa before bringing it back to Delhi. Sonia Gandhi is delighted with the gift and is seen playing with Noorie in the video.

title: Sikkim flood: 8 dead, 22 armymen among 69 missing
description: Besides the 22 army personnel, 47 civilians were also missing, while 166 people have so far been rescued, including an armyman.

title: Will India breach the 100-medal mark in Hangzhou?
description: India, so far, has claimed 81 medals at the ongoing Asian Games that include -- 18 gold, 31 silver and 32 bronze medals. With a total of 12 medals in multiple disciplines, led by athletics events on Day 11, India surpassed their previous best total of 70 medals of Jakarta and Palembang Games in 2018.

title: NCP's Lakshadweep MP disqualified from LS after HC setback
description: Lakshadweep NCP MP Mohammed Faizal has been disqualified from the Lok Sabha after the Kerala high court rejected his plea for suspension of conviction in a murder case. The high court noted that allowing MPs with criminal convictions to continue in office would send the wrong signals to the public. Faizal had been sentenced for attempting to kill a politician during the 2009 Lok Sabha elections.

title: Akshata Murty 'gatecrashes' UK PM Rishi Sunak's speech
description: Akshata Murty, wife of British Prime Minister Rishi Sunak, made a surprise appearance at the Conservative Party conference in Manchester. She revealed that Sunak was unaware of her presence and spoke about their relationship, highlighting his love for the UK and commitment to creating opportunities for others. Murty described Sunak as fun, thoughtful, and compassionate, and emphasized his strength of character and integrity. The unexpected appearance added a personal touch to the conference.

title: Asian Games: With 18 gold medals, India achieve historic first
description: India so far has claimed 81 medals at the ongoing Asian Games that include -- 18 gold, 31 silver and 32 bronze medals. With a total of 12 medals in multiple disciplines, led by athletics events on Day 11, India surpassed their previous best total of 70 medals of Jakarta and Palembang Games in 2018.

title: 6 more deaths reported at Nanded govt hospital in Maha
description: The development came amid the furore caused by the report of 31 patients dying at the hospital in 48 hours earlier this week.

title: 'I had to throw 7 times for gold': Did China try to 'throw' Neeraj out?
description: India's golden boy Neeraj Chopra successfully defended his Asian Games gold in javelin throw with a season's best throw of 88.88m in his fourth attempt but the Chinese officials appeared to have thwarted his chances and targeted the Indian athletes once again.

title: Drug regulator finds toxins in more cough syrups
It is time for us to get secluded and focus on the job: Rohit
description: Indian cricket team will be dealing with a humongous dose of pressure during the World Cup at home, and captain Rohit Sharma said the time has come for the group to 'get secluded' and focus on the job. Rohit wants his team to focus on one match at a time as the World Cup is a long tournament.

title: Marc Marquez, Honda MotoGP divorce brings end to an era
description: After an 11-year partnership, Marc Marquez and Honda Racing Corporation (HRC) have decided to part ways at the end of the 2023 MotoGP season. Marquez, who has won 59 races and six World Championship titles with Honda, has been unable to compete at the front of the field due to the team's lack of a competitive bike. There is speculation that Marquez may join the Gresini Ducati team for the upcoming season. No official announcement has been made regarding Marquez's replacement at Honda.

title: Airlines going bankrupt won't be able to hold onto leased aircraft: Govt
description: Indian carriers going bankrupt in the future will no longer be able to hold on to their leased aircraft and engines under the asset protection (moratorium) provided for a limited time by the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC), like GoAir. A gazette notification by the Union corporate affairs ministry on Tuesday (Oct 3) comes as a huge relief to Indian airlines as the GoAir fiasco had made lenders wary of giving aircraft and engines to them, especially the financially weak ones.

title: ED arrests AAP leader Sanjay Singh in liquor policy case
description: The Enforcement Directorate (ED) on Wednesday arrested AAP MP Sanjay Singh following raids at his house in connection with a money laundering case linked to the Delhi excise policy. Singh's staff members and those linked to him were earlier questioned by the ED in this case. It is alleged that the Delhi government's excise policy for 2021-22 to grant licences to liquor traders allowed cartelisation and favoured certain dealers who had allegedly paid bribes for it, a charge refuted by AAP.

title: Arshad Warsi returns to TV after six years with Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa
description: Arshad Warsi, who was last seen as a judge on Sabse Bada Kalakar, has now joined the judging panel of the upcoming season of Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa.

title: Pak's 'unacceptable behavior' deepens rift with Taliban
description: The already strained ties between Pakistan and Afghanistan have hit a new nadir with Islamabad launching a massive crackdown on illegal migrants in the country, including as many as 1.7 million undocumented Afghans.The order comes as Pakistan grapples with a sharp rise in terror attacks carried out by militants operating from Afghanistan soil, a charge Kabul routinely denies.

title: Watch: Mahira Khan's son walking her down the aisle
description: Pakistani actor Mahira Khan recently got married to her longtime boyfriend Salim Karim in a private ceremony. The wedding pictures show Mahira's son Azlan walking her down the aisle, displaying the bond between them. Mahira shared a video of the wedding on Instagram, where Azlan can be seen participating in the rituals. Fans praised Mahira for raising her son right and expressed admiration for the heartwarming picture of Azlan with his mother.

title: Jr NTR and Janhvi Kapoor's 'Devara' to release in two parts
description: Global star NTR Jr's highly anticipated action drama 'Devara,' directed by Koratala Siva, is set to be released in two parts due to its powerful storyline and grandeur. The film, touted as the biggest release of 2024, is set in coastal India and features a vast canvas that necessitates exploring and establishing characters in depth. While the story remains unchanged, it will thrive in scale across two parts, with the first part scheduled for release on April 5, 2024. This decision has delighted 'Devara' fans worldwide.

title: Ranbir Kapoor summoned by ED in Mahadev betting app case
Caught on cam: US activist stabbed to death in front of girlfriend
description: Ryan Carson, a community activist and poet, was brutally stabbed to death in Brooklyn, New York. The incident occurred as he and his girlfriend were walking home from a wedding. Surveillance footage captured the attack, which showed Carson intervening between his girlfriend and the attacker. Despite pleading for calm, Carson was stabbed multiple times and later died from his injuries. The assailant has not been apprehended, and the investigation is ongoing.

title: Thai mall shooting: '14-yr-old had psychological breakdown'
From Virat to Babar: Top Batters to Watch Out for in ODI WC
description: Cricket aficionados around the globe eagerly await the 2023 ODI World Cup commencing on October 5 in India. With a constellation of cricketing stars set to illuminate the grand stage, let's take a look at some of the most extraordinary batters poised to leave an indelible mark on this edition of the cricketing extravaganza.

title: Govt hikes LPG subsidy for Ujjwala beneficiaries to Rs 300/refill
Trio awarded Chemistry Nobel prize for work on 'quantum dots'
IAF gets first LCA Tejas twin seater aircraft from HAL in boost for 'Aatmanirbhar Bharat'
description: In a boost for "Make in India", Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) on Wednesday handed over the first LCA Tejas twin seater aircraft to the Indian Air Force.HAL has an order of 18 twin seaters from IAF and is planning to deliver eight of them during 2023-24. The remaining 10 would be delivered progressively by 2026-27.

title: 'No signs of abating': Why markets across the globe are falling
ODI WC: Can Cummins emulate Border, Waugh, Ponting & Clarke?
description: Australia are considered the 'boss' of the World Cup, having won five ODI World Cup titles in 12 editions, from 1987 to 2015. Under Allan Border's captaincy, the team won their first title in 1987, and since then they have become the most successful team in the tournament's history. The West Indies and India follow with two titles each.

title: Can England do what only West Indies and Australia have done before?
description: England, the defending champions of the ICC ODI World Cup, have a success rate of 59.75% in the tournament, winning 48 out of 83 matches. They won their only title in 2019, defeating New Zealand in a Super over. In the 2019 edition, Joe Root and Jonny Bairstow both scored over 500 runs, England recorded their highest and second-highest totals, and their runs per over was the best.

title: Facebook plans another job cuts, employees in this division may be sacked today
description: Meta, the parent company of Facebook, is planning to lay off employees in its Reality Labs division's silicon unit focused on metaverse development. The company informed employees of the layoffs through an internal post. The layoffs could potentially impact Mark Zuckerberg's plans for creating augmented and virtual reality products. Meta is also working on advanced AR glasses and smartwatches, with the first version expected to be completed next year. The unit mainly affected is the FAST unit, which designs custom chips for Meta's AR/VR devices. Meta has been cutting jobs to address declining revenue growth and significant losses in the Reality Labs division.

title: How reckless driving caused supercar crash
description: The multiple-vehicle collision involved supercars worth crores, resulting in a Swiss couple losing their lives after their high-end supercar caught fire.

title: Karan Johar announces Koffee With Karan 8
description: Karan Johar will be back with an edgier and more frank season of Koffee with Karan. The new season, which starts on October 26, will feature conversations that go beyond weddings and airport looks. Karan promises to bring out the actors' humorous and unfiltered sides. He dropped a promo for the season, hinting at the new guests that will be featured. Shah Rukh Khan expressed his excitement for the upcoming season.

title: Non-cooperation to ED summons not ground for arrest: SC
description: The Supreme Court was refering to non-conformity of legal provisions while arresting two directors of real estate firm M3M, Pankaj Bansal and Basant Bansal. "A statutory authority is bound by the procedure laid down in the statute and must act within the four corners thereof," it said. "Accused failing to respond to ED's questions would also not be sufficient ground for agency to arrest the person," the top court added.

title: Will pvt capex pick up add to Modi govt's big investment spend?
description: Indian economy is one of the fastest growing major economies in the world and the private sector investment is also showing signs of sustained revival. What is the significance of private capex versus government capex. We explore in this week's TOI Business Bytes episode.

title: Land-for-jobs scam: Court grants bail to Lalu, Rabri & Tejashwi
description: Special judge Geetanjali Goel granted relief to Lalu, Rabri and Tejashwi after they appeared before the court in pursuance of summons issued against them. Ahead of the hearing in the case, Lalu said that hearings keep happening and he is not scared of it as he has not done anything wrong.

title: Watch: Premature celebration costs Korea gold at Asian Games
description: South Korean rollerskater Jung Cheol-won cost his team a gold medal at the Asian Games by celebrating prematurely in the men's 3,000m relay final. Believing he had won, Jung eased up and raised his arms, only to be overtaken by Huang Yu-lin of Taiwan by one hundredth of a second.

title: 2023 ODI World Cup: All major approaching milestones
description: As the ICC ODI World Cup approaches, several players have personal milestones within reach. Trent Boult needs three wickets to reach 200 in ODIs, while Mitchell Starc requires one more wicket to reach 50 in World Cups. Rohit Sharma needs eight sixes to achieve a triple century of sixes in ODIs, and Virat Kohli is set to become the first player to reach 50 ODI centuries.

title: 3 killed as bus crashes into truck on Jaipur-Agra highway
description: At least three people died whereas 24 others were injured after a Jhansi-bound bus collided with a truck parked on the Jaipur-Agra highway on Wednesday. The incident took place at around 2am.

title: NewsClick case: Who is Singham, accused of spreading Chinese propaganda?
description: Neville Roy Singham is an American millionaire who has been accused of spreading Chinese propaganda in India and abroad through his funding network and his IT consulting company, ThoughtWorks. He is said to have close ties with the Chinese government media machine and to have financed several news outlets that promote Beijing's agenda. One of the news outlets that Singham has allegedly funded is NewsClick.

title: NewsClick case: Editor, HR head sent to 7-day police remand
Who'll press power button in the middle for Team India?
description: India's middle order in ODI cricket has been struggling with sub-standard strike rates, leading to poor returns since the 2019 World Cup. The confusion over who bats at No. 4 has been a chronic problem, and the inability to accelerate has been a major issue. Hardik Pandya, Ravindra Jadeja, and KL Rahul, India's designated No. 5, 6, and 7, have seen their strike rates decline.

title: Flash flood in Sikkim after cloud burst; 23 Armymen missing
55 Chinese sailors feared dead in submarine accident: Report
Cops reunite missing parrot worth Rs 1.3L with owner
description: An Australian Galah Cockatoo was reunited with its owner in Hyderabad, India, within three days after it flew away from his house. The bird lover had imported the parrot from Australia for 1.3 lakh rupees. After the bird flew out of its cage, a complaint was lodged with the police, who received information about someone selling the bird on WhatsApp. The bird was handed over to its owner within 24 hours, and no case was registered.

title: TN engineer kills Class XII boy for rejecting his advances
Gayatri and Vikas Oberoi escape safely as their car meets with accident in Italy
description: Actress Gayatri Joshi, of Swades' fame, and her husband Vikas Oberoi, are presently in Italy, where their vehicle was involved in a multi-car accident as part of a collision with several other cars. The couple has escaped unhurt.

title: ED conducts raids at AAP MP Sanjay Singh's residence
